author: news@courierpublicationsllc.com (Staff)
title: Seven Searsport runners compete in Riot Challenge
text:
Seven Searsport runners compete in Riot Challenge By Staff | Oct 12, 2015 
Orono â€” A handful of Searsport cross-country runners participated in the fourth annual Riot Challenge on Friday, Oct. 9. The event was hosted by Orono High School. 
Distance athletes journeyed across the 4-kilometer, or 2.48-mile course. 
The boys team scores were: Orono 25, Foxcroft Academy of Dover-Foxcroft 59, Lee Academy 83, Central of East Corinth 94, Machias 102 and Searsport, Jonesport-Beals and Dexter no score. 
The girls team scores were: Orono 22, Foxcroft Academy 56, Lee Academy 62, Machias 91 and Searsport and Jonesport-Beals no score. 
Orono's Camille Kohtala finished first among the 37 girls in 16:45.80, while Foxcroft Academy's Gabe Piquette placed first among the 45 boys in 14:17.20. 
The individual Searsport girls results were: 21, Audrey Walker, 21:41; 23, Madison Philbrick, 22:01.30; and 37, Thanaporn Cheenthada, 27:13.80. 
The individual Searsport boys results were: 15, Devin Fairbrother, 16:02.60; 19, Holden Clapp, 16:40.40; 26, Malcolm Jones, 17:20.60; and 43, Tony Yang, 21:18. Courier Publications' sports staff can be reached by email at sports@villagesoup.com or by phone at 594-4401.
